main event: Two objects were observed with a fiery red tail near Tillamook, Oregon.
interesting points: The sighting occurred shortly after sunset,The smaller object faded out of sight while the larger one remained visible for a few seconds,There was no physical evidence left from the sighting,The sighting was classified and reviewed by the Air Force,The reliability rating of the report was marked as F-6.
sighted object: two unidentified flying objects with a fiery red tail
witness description: a lighthouse tender at Cape Mears Lighthouse
